8
00:04:08,910 --> 00:04:09,960
What's your name, kiddo?

9
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:10,960
Zhang Wenke.

10
00:04:11,710 --> 00:04:12,750
Where are your parents?

11
00:04:12,870 --> 00:04:13,960
They've gone to work.

12
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,080
Go.

13
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:19,720
What are you doing?

14
00:04:22,070 --> 00:04:24,000
The sheep thieves are here!

15
00:04:25,190 --> 00:04:27,120
The sheep thieves are here!

16
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:28,920
The sheep thieves are here!

17
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:29,560
Stop there!

18
00:04:31,070 --> 00:04:32,190
Give me back my sheep!

19
00:04:33,830 --> 00:04:34,480
Sheep thieves, huh?

20
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:35,510
Give me back my sheep!

21
00:04:37,870 --> 00:04:38,600
Don't move.

22
00:04:38,950 --> 00:04:40,070
I'll break your arm
if you try to resist.

23
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,790
Don't run! Police! Don't move!

24
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:49,200
Don't make me break your arm,

25
00:04:49,550 --> 00:04:50,320
you sheep thief.

26
00:04:50,830 --> 00:04:51,510
Handcuff him!

27
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:53,480
Handcuff him now!

28
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:55,870
Brother!

29
00:04:55,870 --> 00:04:56,560
It hurts.

30
00:05:17,950 --> 00:05:18,390
Here you go.

31
00:05:18,950 --> 00:05:20,240
Come out and help me.

32
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:21,870
Okay.

33
00:05:22,510 --> 00:05:23,240
You go ahead.

34
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:23,680
Eat up.

35
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,190
Enjoy your food and drinks.

36
00:05:24,190 --> 00:05:24,600
All right.

37
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:25,720
Go ahead, Mrs Zhang.

38
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:26,600
We'll help ourselves.

39
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,510
Mother.

40
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:32,120
Tell me

41
00:05:32,310 --> 00:05:33,270
your names.

42
00:05:33,390 --> 00:05:34,070
I'm hungry, too.

43
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:35,950
Do you want some sheep's shit?

44
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:37,830
How many times did you steal it?

45
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,310
Just two or three times.

46
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:41,310
Honestly,

47
00:05:41,310 --> 00:05:42,190
what did you do with the sheep?

48
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:44,360
We killed and sold them.

49
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:50,120
Jianghe

50
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,870
has been with us for a few years now.

51
00:05:53,510 --> 00:05:55,480
He's always been a dedicated

52
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,390
and hard-working man.

53
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:57,950
Well,

54
00:05:58,240 --> 00:05:59,680
the townspeople
have been reporting lately

55
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:01,040
that they've been losing sheep.

56
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:04,510
I brought a few men down to keep watch.

57
00:06:05,190 --> 00:06:06,270
It was hard work.

58
00:06:06,830 --> 00:06:07,950
It's the house ahead.

59
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,000
Chief.

60
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:29,510
Qiusheng.

61
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:31,430
Where's Jianghe?

62
00:06:31,870 --> 00:06:33,000
He's inside.

63
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:33,950
He's inside?

64
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,270
Yes, he is.

65
00:06:35,310 --> 00:06:35,800
Yeah.

66
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:36,630
Jianghe!

67
00:06:39,950 --> 00:06:40,600
Jianghe.

68
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:43,630
Jianghe.

69
00:06:43,630 --> 00:06:44,270
Chief Liang.

70
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:45,160
There's a superior who wants to see you.

71
00:06:45,390 --> 00:06:46,040
Who's it?

72
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,080
Luo Yingwei from the Municipal
Criminal Investigation Department.

73
00:06:52,310 --> 00:06:52,950
Nice to meet you.

74
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:54,160
Nice to meet you.

75
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:55,480
What's the matter?

76
00:06:56,070 --> 00:06:57,430
I came to Kulu County
to investigate a case.

77
00:07:03,270 --> 00:07:04,070
Chief Liang.

78
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:05,630
What's going on here?

79
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,390
Sheep thieves.
We caught them this morning.

80
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:08,390
We're questioning them.

81
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:09,800
Right here?

82
00:07:10,270 --> 00:07:11,430
There's no audio or video recording.

83
00:07:11,830 --> 00:07:13,040
It doesn't comply with
the procedure, does it?

84
00:07:13,510 --> 00:07:14,870
What's going on here?

85
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:16,360
You're not

86
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,000
interrogating them here, are you?

87
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,240
No, Chief Liang.

88
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,390
We're hungry from catching thieves.

89
00:07:20,390 --> 00:07:21,630
So we came for a pot of hot tea.

90
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:23,310
We're taking them back to the station.

91
00:07:23,430 --> 00:07:24,830
Okay, take them back.

92
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:26,430
Let's go!

93
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:30,270
Officer Luo wants to talk to you.

94
00:07:32,390 --> 00:07:33,310
Then how can I go back?

95
00:07:33,430 --> 00:07:35,630
Officer Luo has a car. Don't worry.

96
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:37,920
Officer Luo, you guys talk first.

97
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,270
I'll go back first.

98
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,630
Thank you, Chief Liang.

99
00:07:46,950 --> 00:07:47,600
Have a seat.

100
00:08:03,190 --> 00:08:05,560
I'd like to know more
about the Furnace Homicide

101
00:08:05,630 --> 00:08:07,360
on 26 February in Kulu County.

102
00:08:08,630 --> 00:08:09,430
What would you like to know?

103
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:12,720
Ding Baoyuan,
who was found guilty at the time...

104
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:19,190
Thank you.

105
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,390
He began to appeal the year
after the judgment

106
00:08:25,390 --> 00:08:26,390
came into effect

107
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,390
and has been appealing for seven years.

108
00:08:28,830 --> 00:08:30,430
He's appealed to the Supreme
People's Procuratorate (SPP).

109
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,870
The SPP commissioned the Provincial
Prosecutor's Office to review the case.

110
00:08:35,270 --> 00:08:35,960
Review?

111
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:37,360
It's not necessary.

112
00:08:37,510 --> 00:08:38,440
He's the murderer.

113
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,870
I've read the entire case file,

114
00:08:42,030 --> 00:08:43,840
and there is reasonable doubt
in this case.

115
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:47,200
Director Wei
of the Provincial Office asked us

116
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,080
to review the case.

117
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:49,360
The Provincial Office wants us

118
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:51,630
to review the case
before the comrades

119
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:54,120
from the Provincial
Prosecutor's Office arrive.

120
00:08:55,270 --> 00:08:57,440
We need to re-verify the evidence
from that year,

121
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:58,870
sort out the chain of evidence

122
00:08:58,910 --> 00:09:00,320
and remove reasonable doubt.

123
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:01,960
If it turns out

124
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:03,750
that Ding Baoyuan wasn't the murderer,

125
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:05,480
we'll be able to rectify the situation.

126
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:10,840
My master is the one
working on this case.

127
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:11,960
Is the Provincial Office so distrustful

128
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:13,150
of him?

129
00:09:14,630 --> 00:09:16,030
It's not about trust.

130
00:09:16,030 --> 00:09:16,910
It's about evidence.

131
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:25,510
Mr. Chen Jianghe,

132
00:09:26,150 --> 00:09:27,630
I hope you'll cooperate with me.

133
00:09:30,790 --> 00:09:32,240
Did I say no?

134
00:09:35,390 --> 00:09:36,080
How ridiculous.

135
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:02,720
No signal.

136
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:04,510
You're calling your superior?

137
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:05,550
I've got the signal here.

138
00:10:06,270 --> 00:10:07,630
Report it to your superior now.

139
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:08,790
Thank you.

140
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:17,160
[Fatty Liu]

141
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:25,120
Hello, Commissioner Liu.

142
00:10:26,670 --> 00:10:27,600
Luo Yingwei is speaking.

143
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:28,480
Yes, I've arrived.

144
00:10:29,790 --> 00:10:30,670
He's with me.

145
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:34,720
You know Chen Jianghe's temper
better than I do.

146
00:10:40,150 --> 00:10:41,270
Okay, I got it.

147
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:44,720
The heat has gone.

148
00:10:46,790 --> 00:10:48,030
My superior wants you on the phone.

149
00:10:53,790 --> 00:10:54,440
What?

150
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,270
I don't know about this.

151
00:11:01,270 --> 00:11:02,360
No one told me.

152
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,000
You're the boss.

153
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:16,390
All right.

154
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:25,630
Sorry.

155
00:11:28,390 --> 00:11:29,200
It's okay.

156
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:39,720
Go ahead.

157
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:44,120
Regarding the Furnace Homicide
on 26 February,

158
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:45,480
please tell me the details

159
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:46,790
of the whole case.

160
00:11:46,790 --> 00:11:48,910
Didn't you read the full case file?

161
00:11:48,910 --> 00:11:49,960
I need you to corroborate.

162
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:55,510
It happened on 26 February.

163
00:11:58,030 --> 00:11:59,390
The body fell out of the furnace

164
00:11:59,390 --> 00:12:01,030
between 5:15 AM

165
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:03,000
and 5:25 AM.

166
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:10,670
It was reported at 5:35 AM.

167
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,550
At 6:13 AM, my master arrived
at Heating Station No. 2

168
00:12:15,790 --> 00:12:17,240
with his men.

169
00:12:21,630 --> 00:12:22,600
There was a sandstorm

170
00:12:24,630 --> 00:12:25,480
that day.

171
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:40,270
Hello, honey.

172
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:42,270
I was driving.

173
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:52,870
Go ahead.

174
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:58,480
Nonsense.

175
00:12:58,720 --> 00:12:59,840
I'll try my best.

176
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:01,320
Honey, I got it.

177
00:13:03,510 --> 00:13:04,480
You've taken the trouble.

178
00:13:05,150 --> 00:13:06,120
Thank you for your hard work.

179
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:07,150
I'm going to inspect a crime scene.

180
00:13:22,030 --> 00:13:22,840
My rhinitis is acting up.

181
00:14:39,910 --> 00:14:41,790
I've never seen anything like this.

182
00:14:42,030 --> 00:14:43,030
It's scary.

183
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:44,440
When did this truck arrive?

184
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:45,790
Has it been here the whole time?

185
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:47,670
It arrived at 5:30 AM.

186
00:14:47,870 --> 00:14:48,790
It's a coal truck.

187
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:55,550
How do you get to work everyday?

188
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:57,200
I come by bike

189
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:58,630
every day.

190
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:00,750
What were you doing last night?

191
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:02,200
There's been a murder.

192
00:15:03,790 --> 00:15:04,960
Who let them in?

193
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:09,240
Well, I let them in.

194
00:15:09,840 --> 00:15:10,720
They're here to deliver coal.

195
00:15:11,390 --> 00:15:12,200
There's a rule at the factory

196
00:15:12,390 --> 00:15:13,840
that the coal must be unloaded
when it arrives.

197
00:15:16,630 --> 00:15:17,720
Who discovered the body first?

198
00:15:18,390 --> 00:15:19,870
The two workers on the night shift.

199
00:15:19,870 --> 00:15:21,080
That's Mr. Liu.

200
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:22,360
That kid is Wang Liang.

201
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,200
Who are those guys?

202
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:30,550
The two in uniforms

203
00:15:30,550 --> 00:15:31,910
are the day shift workers,

204
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:34,000
the other two are the coal drivers.

205
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:35,840
Tell me about your station.

206
00:15:36,510 --> 00:15:37,790
There are seven of us

207
00:15:37,790 --> 00:15:39,750
at the heating station, including me.

208
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:41,480
Six workers in three shifts.

209
00:15:41,510 --> 00:15:42,600
I'm in charge.

210
00:15:43,320 --> 00:15:44,240
Last night,

211
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:45,270
Mr. Liu

212
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:48,000
and his apprentice were
on the night shift.

213
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:49,670
Only three of us were in the station.

214
00:15:50,030 --> 00:15:51,670
In the morning, when the slag came out,

215
00:15:51,910 --> 00:15:53,550
a body suddenly fell out.

216
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:57,200
Can outsiders come in?

217
00:15:57,480 --> 00:15:59,080
Outsiders can't get in.

218
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:00,600
This gate

219
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:01,790
is locked from the inside.

220
00:16:02,790 --> 00:16:04,600
There's only one key,

221
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:05,750
and I have it all the time.

222
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,320
I usually lock the gate

223
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:09,000
at 10 PM when the night shift workers

224
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,080
take over.

225
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:12,360
But last night, I was a bit late,

226
00:16:12,390 --> 00:16:13,600
I locked it around 11 PM.

227
00:16:13,910 --> 00:16:14,670
Why?

228
00:16:14,870 --> 00:16:16,080
What's the point of having strict rules

229
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:17,510
for a furnace room?

230
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:19,600
It's mainly because we're afraid
of losing coal.

231
00:16:19,670 --> 00:16:21,000
A lot of people around here

232
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:22,120
can't afford to install heaters,

233
00:16:22,320 --> 00:16:25,200
so they burn coal
in their cookers to keep warm.

234
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:26,960
In the worst cases,
half a truckload of coal

235
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:28,200
can be lost.

236
00:16:28,270 --> 00:16:30,870
We'll have to pay for all the damage.

237
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:32,440
If outsiders aren't allowed in,

238
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:34,840
can the people inside get out?

239
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:36,360
No, they can't.

240
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:37,790
There's been a case

241
00:16:37,790 --> 00:16:39,390
where a night shift worker
snuck out for a drink

242
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:40,790
and the furnace went out.

243
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:43,270
And there's been a case of stealing coal

244
00:16:43,270 --> 00:16:44,960
by the station staff.

245
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:47,600
How can you be sure
there's only one key?

246
00:16:49,910 --> 00:16:50,790
When the new lock was bought,

247
00:16:50,790 --> 00:16:52,120
only one was given
to the station manager.

248
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:54,000
The rest were destroyed in public.

249
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:56,510
Several of us station managers
have shared experiences,

250
00:16:56,510 --> 00:16:57,270
so we all do the same.

251
00:16:58,600 --> 00:16:59,240
Captain Ge,

252
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:00,720
there are some footprints.

253
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:02,550
No sign of dragging.

254
00:17:02,910 --> 00:17:04,550
The crime scene has been
too badly damaged.

255
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:08,000
Check this wall

256
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:09,590
for signs of climbing.

257
00:17:09,590 --> 00:17:10,550
Okay, I'll check it now.

258
00:17:23,510 --> 00:17:24,200
Captain Ge,

259
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:26,480
the body was so badly burnt,

260
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:29,070
the preliminary judgment
is that it's a woman.

261
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:55,720
Mr. Ge.

262
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:57,480
How's it? Are you feeling better?

263
00:17:57,880 --> 00:17:58,790
Yes.

264
00:18:00,110 --> 00:18:01,350
Take him inside and question him.

265
00:18:01,550 --> 00:18:02,110
Okay.

266
00:18:03,550 --> 00:18:04,240
Thank you.

267
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:08,960
You know this kid?

268
00:18:11,590 --> 00:18:12,830
He's also from Luoche like you.

269
00:18:16,590 --> 00:18:18,030
It's a small society

270
00:18:18,880 --> 00:18:20,110
within these walls.

271
00:18:21,310 --> 00:18:23,720
Other people may think nothing
of a job at a heating station.

272
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:26,070
But it's a good job

273
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:28,790
in this small county.

274
00:18:29,830 --> 00:18:30,750
It's a secure job.

275
00:18:40,790 --> 00:18:41,920
So far,

276
00:18:42,590 --> 00:18:44,000
we haven't received a report.

277
00:18:44,310 --> 00:18:46,880
So we can't confirm
the victim's identity.

278
00:18:47,830 --> 00:18:49,790
According
to the preliminary forensic results,

279
00:18:49,790 --> 00:18:51,070
[Furnace Homicide]
the victim is a woman

280
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:53,110
in her thirties,

281
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:55,680
about 1.6 metres tall

282
00:18:56,070 --> 00:18:57,590
and weighs about 50 kilos.

283
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:01,160
But the exact cause of death
could not be confirmed.

284
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:04,400
Wang, tell us more about it.

285
00:19:05,590 --> 00:19:07,590
Due to the fact that the victim's
epidermis and part of her torso

286
00:19:07,590 --> 00:19:08,750
had been burnt,

287
00:19:08,790 --> 00:19:10,480
no superficial injuries were visible.

288
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:12,480
The trace of soot in the victim's lungs

289
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:13,790
can be explained by the fact

290
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:15,720
that the victim
may have been breathing lightly

291
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:17,440
when she was stuffed
into the furnace.

292
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:18,830
It can also be explained

293
00:19:18,830 --> 00:19:20,640
as a natural formation

294
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:21,680
during prolonged combustion processes.

295
00:19:22,510 --> 00:19:25,400
Heating Station No. 2
is a completely enclosed environment.

296
00:19:26,310 --> 00:19:27,270
The general rule is

297
00:19:27,270 --> 00:19:28,920
that no one is allowed to go out

298
00:19:28,920 --> 00:19:30,270
after 10 PM.

299
00:19:30,830 --> 00:19:33,240
The key is in the hands
of station manager, Ding Baoyuan.

300
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:36,720
The heating station
is surrounded by a tall fence.

301
00:19:36,790 --> 00:19:38,240
No signs of climbing were found

302
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:40,000
after the scene investigation.

303
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:43,400
[Ding Baiyuan, Liu Sancheng, Wang Liang]
These three were on duty last night.

304
00:19:43,480 --> 00:19:45,590
Ding Baoyuan is 44 years old.

305
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:47,790
He used to work at the power station.

306
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:49,480
A year ago, he was injured at work

307
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:51,590
and transferred to the heating station.

308
00:19:51,790 --> 00:19:54,270
During the seven-month heating period,

309
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:56,790
the station manager has to live and eat
at the heating station

310
00:19:56,790 --> 00:19:57,830
and lead the shifts.

311
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:01,160
The rule is that the station manager
must be on duty

312
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:02,200
24 hours a day.

313
00:20:03,030 --> 00:20:04,720
But the factory knows

314
00:20:04,830 --> 00:20:06,680
that the station manager
has family and commitments.

315
00:20:08,830 --> 00:20:09,510
Here.

316
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:11,160
Have some water.

317
00:20:12,750 --> 00:20:13,550
Hence,

318
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:16,510
as long as the station manager
is on duty at night,

319
00:20:16,920 --> 00:20:19,270
he can go out during the day.

320
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:23,110
I went out last night around 9 PM

321
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:24,830
and came back around 11 PM.

322
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:27,160
When I got back, I locked the gate

323
00:20:27,590 --> 00:20:29,200
and went round the furnace room,

324
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:30,350
then I came back to bed.

325
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:31,880
I slept

326
00:20:32,070 --> 00:20:33,030
until Wang Liang called me at dawn.

327
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:35,400
He called you twice before you got up.

328
00:20:36,110 --> 00:20:38,480
He told you something bad happened.
Why didn't you get up right away?

329
00:20:38,590 --> 00:20:39,790
Wang Liang

330
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:40,960
didn't make it clear either.

331
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:42,510
I didn't think
it would be such a big deal.

332
00:20:42,510 --> 00:20:43,790
I thought he was just kidding around.

333
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:46,440
Why did you let the coal truck in

334
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,830
when there was a murder?

335
00:20:49,720 --> 00:20:51,440
When I woke up,
the truck was already there,

336
00:20:51,440 --> 00:20:52,640
and the drivers
were banging on the gate.

337
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:54,510
We have a rule at the factory

338
00:20:54,510 --> 00:20:56,310
that the coal has to be unloaded
when it arrives.

339
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:58,350
[Safety First]
Hello? Police station?

340
00:20:58,590 --> 00:20:59,920
- I want to report a crime.
- Open the gate!

341
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:01,920
This is Heating Station No. 2.

342
00:21:02,110 --> 00:21:02,640
Yes.

343
00:21:03,070 --> 00:21:05,510
Hello? This is Heating Station No. 2!

344
00:21:08,510 --> 00:21:09,640
Here comes the coal truck.

345
00:21:11,070 --> 00:21:13,960
Liu Sancheng and Wang Liang
are the master and apprentice.

346
00:21:14,110 --> 00:21:15,790
[Liu Sancheng: Staff, Wang Liang: Staff]
Liu Sancheng is 54 years old,

347
00:21:15,790 --> 00:21:16,880
Wang Liang is 20 years old.

348
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:18,880
They were the two
on night duty last night.

349
00:21:19,270 --> 00:21:21,510
The body was stuffed into the furnace

350
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:23,310
while they were on duty.

351
00:21:23,680 --> 00:21:26,720
There's no sign
of it being any different than usual.

352
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:29,590
Wang Liang and I took over our shift,

353
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,550
filled the furnace with coal,

354
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:33,440
and sat down to play chess.

355
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,550
Nothing happened all night.

356
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:36,640
But

357
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:39,680
who knew, when the slag came out,

358
00:21:40,110 --> 00:21:42,350
we saw that.

359
00:21:42,510 --> 00:21:44,550
Didn't you see anyone come in or out?

360
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:45,880
No.

361
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:48,680
We keep the gate locked at night.

362
00:21:49,030 --> 00:21:51,750
The key is with the station manager.

363
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:56,240
It was about 11 PM

364
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:57,590
when he came back from outside.

365
00:21:57,790 --> 00:21:59,640
He chatted with us

366
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:02,830
and went to bed on the first floor.

367
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,830
His quarters are on the second floor
of the furnace room.

368
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:11,830
Did he go out last night?

369
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:12,960
No.

370
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:18,310
Well, we were busy with the furnace

371
00:22:18,310 --> 00:22:19,440
and playing chess,

372
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:21,720
so we didn't pay any attention
to the outside.

373
00:22:24,110 --> 00:22:28,350
Yeah, it was about 9 PM.

374
00:22:29,030 --> 00:22:30,240
At 9 PM,

375
00:22:30,880 --> 00:22:32,000
he went out

376
00:22:32,070 --> 00:22:33,030
across the yard.

377
00:22:33,590 --> 00:22:34,510
But he

378
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:36,310
is the station manager.

379
00:22:36,510 --> 00:22:38,960
He won't tell us
if he has anything to do.

380
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:42,200
Are the light bulbs in the yard fine?

381
00:22:42,310 --> 00:22:43,440
They're lit up at night, right?

382
00:22:46,310 --> 00:22:47,110
Right.

383
00:22:51,070 --> 00:22:51,960
Is the door closed at night

384
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:52,790
when there's no sun?

385
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:55,920
I closed the door.

386
00:23:06,270 --> 00:23:07,160
Where did you sit?

387
00:23:16,270 --> 00:23:18,790
Can't you hear anything at night?

388
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:24,880
We were focused on our chess game.

389
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:27,550
Besides, this furnace

390
00:23:27,550 --> 00:23:28,480
makes a lot of noise.

391
00:23:29,750 --> 00:23:31,790
We can't hear anything.

392
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:38,920
I was sitting here.

393
00:23:42,750 --> 00:23:43,680
How many rounds did you play?

394
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:45,790
Three.

395
00:23:47,720 --> 00:23:48,510
Did you win

396
00:23:48,680 --> 00:23:49,350
or lose?

397
00:23:50,030 --> 00:23:50,830
I won.

398
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:52,400
How many rounds did you win?

399
00:23:52,680 --> 00:23:53,680
Three.

400
00:23:55,680 --> 00:23:56,720
You lost three rounds?

401
00:23:59,790 --> 00:24:00,510
You're his master.

402
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:03,000
That won't do.

403
00:24:03,960 --> 00:24:06,750
The furnace's coal inlet was so small,

404
00:24:07,550 --> 00:24:10,070
so the body had to be shoved
through the rear slag box.

405
00:24:10,440 --> 00:24:11,510
We've done experiments.

406
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:13,310
It takes a certain amount of skill

407
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:15,750
to open the rear slag box

408
00:24:15,750 --> 00:24:17,110
and shove a 50-kg body in there

409
00:24:17,400 --> 00:24:18,750
and turn it around in the furnace.

410
00:24:19,070 --> 00:24:21,400
It was probably done
by the station staff.

411
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:23,590
Six sets of footprints have been
identified in the furnace room.

412
00:24:23,830 --> 00:24:25,880
So far, five sets of footprints
have been identified

413
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:28,110
as belonging to the three men
who were on duty that night

414
00:24:28,830 --> 00:24:30,680
and the two men
who delivered the coal the next morning.

415
00:24:30,830 --> 00:24:32,000
According to them,

416
00:24:32,160 --> 00:24:33,310
after discovering the body,

417
00:24:33,550 --> 00:24:35,110
Wang Liang called for Ding Baoyuan,

418
00:24:35,110 --> 00:24:36,510
and he ran in to check it out.

419
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:38,400
At that moment, the coal truck arrived.

420
00:24:38,750 --> 00:24:40,720
The coal drivers heard
that a body had fallen

421
00:24:41,030 --> 00:24:42,310
and came in to see what was going on.

422
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:43,480
The on-site investigation

423
00:24:43,590 --> 00:24:45,200
proved the process they said it was.

424
00:24:48,750 --> 00:24:49,510
Well,

425
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:52,480
the sixth set of footprints
are unidentifiable?

426
00:24:52,830 --> 00:24:53,680
The sixth set of footprints

427
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:55,750
had been trampled
and covered almost completely

428
00:24:55,750 --> 00:24:57,480
with soot by the fifth set.

429
00:24:57,680 --> 00:24:58,350
Jianghe,

430
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:00,160
what do you think about it?

431
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:02,790
Two points are worth noting.

432
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:04,110
The first point is

433
00:25:04,310 --> 00:25:06,240
whether the victim was completely dead

434
00:25:06,310 --> 00:25:07,310
and stuffed in the oven

435
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:10,720
or whether there are
still signs of life.

436
00:25:11,200 --> 00:25:14,160
The second point is to determine
the gender of the sixth set of footprints.

437
00:25:14,350 --> 00:25:15,000
Ge,

438
00:25:15,790 --> 00:25:18,110
looks like these three
from that night are the best suspects.

439
00:25:18,510 --> 00:25:19,920
Let's start with them.

440
00:25:22,310 --> 00:25:23,240
From what I've read in the case file,

441
00:25:23,240 --> 00:25:24,160
you guys had been pinning

442
00:25:24,160 --> 00:25:26,000
your suspicions
on Ding Baoyuan from the beginning.

443
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:26,790
Why?

444
00:25:27,750 --> 00:25:28,920
The three of them,

445
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:31,640
Liu Sancheng and Wang Liang
are witnesses to each other,

446
00:25:31,640 --> 00:25:32,960
but no one can bear witness
to Ding Baoyuan.

447
00:25:33,680 --> 00:25:34,750
Liu Sancheng and Wang Liang

448
00:25:34,750 --> 00:25:36,160
could be working together
to commit the crime.

449
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:37,720
How's that possible?

450
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:38,790
If the two of them worked together,

451
00:25:38,790 --> 00:25:40,030
when the body fell out,

452
00:25:40,030 --> 00:25:41,590
they could've just stuffed it
into the furnace

453
00:25:41,920 --> 00:25:43,000
and burnt it to ashes.

454
00:25:43,110 --> 00:25:44,550
How could they still
wake up Ding Baoyuan?

455
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:45,590
What else?

456
00:25:45,880 --> 00:25:46,680
Besides,

457
00:25:46,790 --> 00:25:49,070
the only key was on Ding Baoyuan.

458
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:52,960
Ding Baoyuan was called twice
before he woke up,

459
00:25:53,680 --> 00:25:56,310
and more importantly,
he let the coal truck in.

460
00:25:56,480 --> 00:25:57,480
The workers unloaded the coal

461
00:25:57,480 --> 00:25:59,400
and went inside the furnace room
to look at the body.

462
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:01,720
The crime scene
was completely destroyed.

463
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:05,400
What you're saying
can only be called suspicion,

464
00:26:05,880 --> 00:26:07,110
not evidence.

465
00:26:12,960 --> 00:26:15,270
You've read the case file.

466
00:26:15,270 --> 00:26:16,400
What does it say?

467
00:26:16,830 --> 00:26:18,790
Ding Baoyuan let the coal truck in
early in the morning.

468
00:26:18,790 --> 00:26:20,030
Several workers unloaded the coal.

469
00:26:20,030 --> 00:26:21,790
They destroyed all the evidence
at the crime scene.

470
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:24,000
It's already written like this.
Is it still a suspicion?

471
00:26:24,160 --> 00:26:25,920
I'm talking about physical evidence,

472
00:26:26,070 --> 00:26:27,920
not speculation based on facts.

473
00:26:31,590 --> 00:26:33,240
A sandstorm is coming!

474
00:26:33,550 --> 00:26:35,110
Get the sheep back here now!

475
00:26:38,160 --> 00:26:38,960
Run!

476
00:26:39,240 --> 00:26:40,070
Run!

477
00:26:40,400 --> 00:26:40,750
Run!

478
00:26:40,750 --> 00:26:41,750
Honey, run!

479
00:26:57,270 --> 00:26:58,110
Where are you going?

480
00:27:02,350 --> 00:27:03,160
Qiusheng.

481
00:27:04,880 --> 00:27:07,270
Move forward.

482
00:27:22,160 --> 00:27:23,310
Could you tell me more

483
00:27:23,310 --> 00:27:25,310
about the process
of identifying the victim?

484
00:27:28,350 --> 00:27:29,480
Kulu isn't a big county,

485
00:27:30,110 --> 00:27:31,310
but it's got a lot of transients.

486
00:27:33,880 --> 00:27:35,030
We couldn't

487
00:27:36,160 --> 00:27:37,070
identify

488
00:27:37,160 --> 00:27:39,680
the victim for three days.

489
00:27:40,110 --> 00:27:41,550
It was only on the fourth day
that we made any progress.

490
00:27:52,160 --> 00:27:52,720
Captain Ge.

491
00:27:59,880 --> 00:28:00,550
Master,

492
00:28:01,110 --> 00:28:02,960
I'm almost breaking my legs
from investigating the case.

493
00:28:03,110 --> 00:28:03,920
How's it?

494
00:28:04,270 --> 00:28:05,680
The victim's been identified?

495
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:06,400
No.

496
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:09,270
I've been to ten neighbourhood
associations this morning.

497
00:28:09,270 --> 00:28:10,510
Nobody's reported it.

498
00:28:10,640 --> 00:28:11,750
I think she lived alone.

499
00:28:13,070 --> 00:28:13,750
What do you reckon?

500
00:28:14,640 --> 00:28:16,590
We have a permanent population
of 22,000 people.

501
00:28:16,750 --> 00:28:18,160
It's strange if a family doesn't notice

502
00:28:18,160 --> 00:28:19,070
a missing person

503
00:28:19,070 --> 00:28:19,920
for two or three days.

504
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:21,750
That's why I think she lived alone.

505
00:28:22,030 --> 00:28:23,920
Captain Ge, this woman reported

506
00:28:23,920 --> 00:28:25,920
her widowed daughter-in-law,
Cheng Chun,

507
00:28:26,030 --> 00:28:27,160
missing.

508
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:32,160
DNA later

509
00:28:32,400 --> 00:28:34,110
proved that the victim was Cheng Chun.

510
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:36,200
As we were about to investigate

511
00:28:36,200 --> 00:28:38,110
her movements and social connections,

512
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:40,000
something suddenly happened.

513
00:28:40,110 --> 00:28:40,920
What's it?

514
00:28:42,160 --> 00:28:43,310
Ding Baoyuan ran away.

515
00:28:48,790 --> 00:28:49,480
Who's there?

516
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:54,750
Hi, we're from the police station
in Kulu County.

517
00:28:55,030 --> 00:28:55,830
Is Ding Baoyuan home?

518
00:28:56,110 --> 00:28:56,720
No.

519
00:29:01,110 --> 00:29:01,790
Since Ding Baoyuan isn't here,

520
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:02,920
you have to come with us.

521
00:29:03,720 --> 00:29:04,510
Where to?

522
00:29:06,070 --> 00:29:08,510
[Wanted Notice]
Things went easy when he ran away.

523
00:29:09,750 --> 00:29:11,790
You're pregnant. Sit down.

524
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:14,790
Make sure she sits down.

525
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:15,920
Help her.

526
00:29:21,590 --> 00:29:23,960
Calm down. I just want
to ask you some questions.

527
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:26,200
What time did he go
to your house yesterday

528
00:29:26,200 --> 00:29:27,000
to pack his things?

529
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:29,920
It's about night time,

530
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:35,110
11 PM or 12 PM.

531
00:29:36,030 --> 00:29:37,000
Be precise.

532
00:29:42,790 --> 00:29:43,590
Mister.

533
00:29:45,680 --> 00:29:47,110
Boss, have you seen him lately?

534
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:48,400
Try to remember.

535
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:53,310
I've seen him over there.

536
00:29:53,880 --> 00:29:54,480
Have you seen

537
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:55,550
this person?

538
00:29:58,920 --> 00:30:01,350
After a month-long manhunt,

539
00:30:01,590 --> 00:30:04,110
Ding Baoyuan turned up

540
00:30:04,110 --> 00:30:04,880
in his hometown.

541
00:30:05,400 --> 00:30:08,200
He used Cheng Chun's bank card

542
00:30:08,400 --> 00:30:11,240
[China Post, Postal Savings Bank]
at an ATM.

543
00:30:11,720 --> 00:30:13,960
My master took us there in a hurry.

544
00:30:14,590 --> 00:30:16,310
The crippled man is Ding Baoyuan.

545
00:30:21,270 --> 00:30:23,000
There's no surveillance at the ATM?

546
00:30:23,110 --> 00:30:24,000
We don't have surveillance

547
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:25,920
on this ATM yet.

548
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:36,680
Madam,

549
00:30:37,790 --> 00:30:39,830
how long have you been
setting up your stall here?

550
00:30:39,830 --> 00:30:41,200
A couple of years.

551
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:43,200
Have you seen this man before?

552
00:30:45,110 --> 00:30:45,920
Yes, I have.

553
00:30:46,750 --> 00:30:47,550
When?

554
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:50,000
The day before yesterday,
he came to buy buns from me.

555
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:52,070
He's got mean eyes.

556
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:54,880
Are you telling the truth?

557
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:55,790
How can you be sure?

558
00:30:56,550 --> 00:30:57,960
He's on the wanted notice.

559
00:30:57,960 --> 00:30:59,240
He's a cripple, isn't he?

560
00:30:59,240 --> 00:31:00,110
Why didn't you call the police?

